# zbitx delta packages, installed on top of Raspberry Pi OS Desktop (stage4).
# Anything stock Raspberry Pi OS already ships (iw, wireless-regdb, the Pixel
# desktop + its add-ons, pi-bluetooth, cloud-guest-utils/init_resize, the
# build base) is intentionally NOT listed here — that is the whole point of
# moving to pi-gen. Recommends are ON in pi-gen, so no curated add-on lists.

# --- zbitx build toolchain ---
build-essential
pkg-config
git
ca-certificates
wget
curl

# --- zbitxv2 build/runtime deps (from upstream install.txt) ---
libncurses-dev
libasound2-dev
libgtk-3-dev
libsqlite3-dev
sqlite3
# FFTW3 double + single precision (Bookworm ships 3.3.10, == upstream latest).
libfftw3-dev
libfftw3-single3

# --- WiFi access point stack (hybrid model) ---
# NetworkManager (stock) keeps wlan0 as the client so Raspberry Pi Imager WiFi
# provisioning works. hostapd + dnsmasq run the zbitx AP on the virtual uap0
# interface; NM is told to leave uap0 unmanaged (99-zbitx-uap0-unmanaged.conf).
# dhcpcd is deliberately NOT installed — uap0.service assigns the AP's static
# IP itself, and NM owns wlan0.
hostapd
dnsmasq
iptables
iptables-persistent
